<subSubSection id="9AA9651CFFC7FFEBA08678AF927E0E7F" box="[399,542,1013,1038]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226" type="description">
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFC7FFEBA08678AF927E0E7F" blockId="14.[399,542,1013,1038]" box="[399,542,1013,1038]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226">(41 SPECIES)</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9AA9651CFFC7FFEBA1AA7F4492BA0CC2" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFC7FFEBA1AA7F4492E90FF5" blockId="14.[163,779,1053,1412]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC7FFEBA1AA7F4491780E42" box="[163,280,1054,1075]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Ammoniacal and weakly muscled 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC7FFEBA39F7F47936B0E42" authorityName="D' ORBIGNY" authorityYear="1845" box="[662,779,1053,1075]" class="Cephalopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226" phylum="Mollusca" rank="order">Oegopsida</taxonomicName>
with a secondary adult tentacular club but with primary tentacle club in early stages, with protective membranes on clubs symmetrical or subsymmetrical, without carpal locking apparatus, without keel, without terminal pad; buccal connectives attach ventrally to ventral arms; funnel–mantle locking apparatus usually oval, although sometimes modified by projections (tragus and/or antitragus), reaching the anterior margin of the mantle; fins usually terminal; often with a long tail supported by the secondary conus of the gladius during some stages of development.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFC7FFEBA1AA7EF292BA0CC2" blockId="14.[163,779,1448,1715]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC7FFEBA1AA7EF2916C0FCC" box="[163,268,1448,1469]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226">Remarks:</emphasis>
Tragus and antitragus refer to two protruding knobs found in the funnel–mantle locking apparatus of some 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC7FFEBA1ED7EBF91C00F8A" authorityName="GRAY" authorityYear="1849" box="[228,416,1509,1531]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Chiroteuthoidea">Chiroteuthoidea</taxonomicName>
; see 
<bibRefCitation id="B6224B66FFC7FFEBA0DE7EBC936A0F8A" author="Vecchione M &amp; Young RE" box="[471,778,1509,1531]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226" refId="ref17571" refString="Vecchione M, Young RE. 2019 c. Neoteuthis thielei Naef, 1921. Version 26 March 2019 (under construction). Available at: http: // tolweb. org / Neoteuthis _ thielei / 19926 / 2019.03.26" type="url" year="2019">Young &amp; Vecchione (2019c)</bibRefCitation>
for more information. Adults of the paedomorphic genus 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC7FFEBA1E77D78924B0C49" authority="Pfeffer, 1912" authorityName="Pfeffer" authorityYear="1912" box="[238,555,1570,1592]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Chiroteuthidae" genus="Planctoteuthis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC7FFEBA1E77D7891F30C46" box="[238,403,1570,1591]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226">Planctoteuthis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B6224B66FFC7FFEBA0927D78924B0C49" author="Pfeffer G" box="[411,555,1570,1592]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226" pagination="1 - 815" refId="ref16383" refString="Pfeffer G. 1912. Die Cephalopoden der Plankton-Expedition. Zugleich eine monographische ubersicht der Oegopsiden Cephalopoden. Ergebnisse der Plankton-Expedition der Humboldt-stiftung 2: 1 - 815." type="journal article" year="1912">Pfeffer, 1912</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
retain the primary club; hence, the morphological characters related to the tentacle morphology in this diagnosis do not apply to this genus. The funnel–mantle locking apparatus of 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC7FFEBA1AA7DC792170CC2" authority="(Verany, 1839)" baseAuthorityName="Verany" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[163,631,1693,1715]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Chiroteuthidae" genus="Grimalditeuthis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bonplandi">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC7FFEBA1AA7DC791AF0CC3" box="[163,463,1693,1714]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226">Grimalditeuthis bonplandi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="B6224B66FFC7FFEBA0D47DC7920F0CC2" author="Verany JB" box="[477,623,1693,1715]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226" pagination="91 - 98" refId="ref17612" refString="Verany JB. 1839. Memoire sur six nouvelles especes de Cephalopodes trouves dans la Mediterranee a Nice. Memorie della Reale Accademia delle Scienze di Torino 1: 91 - 98." type="journal article" year="1839">Vérany, 1839</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is fused.
</paragraph>
